9. Conclusions & Overall Assessment
Overall Assessment:
  • Study Design: This was a cardiovascular pharmacology study (Cardiovascular Safety Pharmacology) in DOG BEAGLE (6 animals) via oral gavage administration. Primary focus: cardiovascular effects and exposure-response relationships.
  • Mortality: All animals survived to scheduled sacrifice.
  • Body Weights: No significant treatment-related effects.
  • Body Temperature: Statistically significant temperature differences were observed between groups.
  • Cardiovascular: No statistically significant changes in hemodynamic parameters.
  • ECG: No statistically significant changes in ECG parameters.
  • Pharmacokinetics: Pharmacokinetic summary: Drug-X - 0/20/50/150 mg Drug-..: Cmax=213.00 ug/mL at Day 36.0; 0/50/20/150 mg Drug-..: Cmax=445.00 ug/mL at Day 36.0; 150/20/50/0 mg Drug-..: Cmax=354.00 ug/mL at Day 1.0; 15
  • Pathology: Macroscopic and microscopic pathology data were not included in this SEND dataset.
  • Data Gaps: The following domains were not available: Food/Water Consumption, Macroscopic Pathology, Microscopic Pathology, Organ Weights.
Preliminary NOAEL Assessment (Crossover Design)
NOAEL: 150 mg/kg
LOAEL: None
Route: ORAL GAVAGE
Species: DOG BEAGLE

Rationale

  • NOAEL: 150 mg/kg (highest dose tested). No adverse findings identified at any dose level in this crossover study.
  • In this crossover design, NOAEL is assessed per dose level across all periods. Within-subject variability is accounted for by the design. Dose levels: 20 mg/kg, 50 mg/kg, 150 mg/kg.

Important Caveats:
  • Crossover study design: each animal receives multiple dose levels across periods. NOAEL assessment is based on within-subject comparisons rather than between-group analysis.
  • This is an automated preliminary assessment based on statistical significance (p < 0.05) without multiplicity adjustment. A qualified toxicologist should review all findings for biological relevance, dose-response patterns, and clinical significance.
  • Individual animal data, historical control ranges, and full pathology peer review were not incorporated into this automated assessment.
Analytical Methods: Descriptive statistics (mean, SD, SE) for continuous endpoints. One-way ANOVA for overall group comparisons; Student's t-test for pairwise vs. control. Incidence tables for pathology findings. Significance: alpha = 0.05, no multiplicity adjustment. Analysis performed using Python (scipy.stats, pandas, matplotlib).
